{
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "title: \"Early Childhood Services in Victoria: Data Trends and Breakdown\"\n",
        "toc: true\n",
        "toc-location: body\n",
        "format:\n",
        "  closeread-html:\n",
        "    code-fold: true\n",
        "    cr-style:\n",
        "      narrative-background-color: \"#ffffff\"\n",
        "      narrative-background-color-sidebar: \"#ffffff\"\n",
        "      section-background-color: \"#ffffff\"\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "This scrolly telling document outlines the performance of Victorian early childhood education and care services against the National Quality Standard (NQS) over the past decade. The analysis is based on data sourced from the Australian Childrens' Education & Care Quality Authority's (ACECQA) National Quality Standard datasets. \n",
        "\n",
        "This analysis is broken into two sections: service quality and service count.  "
      ],
      "id": "2a668f0e"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "message": false
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: setup\n",
        "#| warning: false\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "from script.plotting import plot_nqs_performance, plot_rating_distribution_1, plot_seifa_distribution, plot_service_counts_timeseries, plot_management_type_stack, plot_management_split_comparison\n",
        "\n",
        "final_df = pd.read_csv('script/NQAITS_Quarterly_Data.csv', parse_dates=['Source_Quarter'])\n",
        "final_df_vic = final_df[final_df['Managing Jurisdiction'] == 'VIC']"
      ],
      "id": "setup",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Service Quality\n",
        ":::{.cr-section}\n",
        "::: {#cr-plot-rating-yoy style=\"width: 1000px; height: 500px;\"}"
      ],
      "id": "8f1a749b"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "fig = plot_nqs_performance(final_df_vic, show_yoy=False)\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "4464ce23",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "Almost 90% of services are meeting or exceeding the NQS, with sessional services exceeding LDC by 8% pt.   @cr-plot-rating-yoy\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {#cr-plot-rating-noyoy style=\"width: 1000px; height: 500px;\"}"
      ],
      "id": "e4f79187"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "fig = plot_nqs_performance(final_df_vic, show_yoy=True)\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "618e790a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "Change in this figure remains low, sitting around +1% YoY for Q4 2025. @cr-plot-rating-noyoy\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {#cr-plot-rating-dist-full style=\"width: 1000px; height: 500px;\"}"
      ],
      "id": "722ac087"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "fig = plot_rating_distribution_1(final_df_vic, highlight_rating = None)\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "e8fbb1e2",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "Most services that are not meeting the NQS are either for-profit or on-site (state school) services. @cr-plot-rating-dist-full\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {#cr-plot-rating-dist-highlighted style=\"width: 1000px; height: 500px;\"}"
      ],
      "id": "cc56c388"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "fig = plot_rating_distribution_1(final_df_vic, highlight_rating='Exceeding NQS')\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "dba6e3b5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "Non-profits tend to have a higher proportion of services that exceed the NQS, especially for co-located services (state and independet).@cr-plot-rating-dist-highlighted\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {#cr-plot-rating-SEIFA-full style=\"width: 1000px; height: 500px;\"}"
      ],
      "id": "4e76e291"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "fig = plot_seifa_distribution(final_df_vic, highlight_rating = None)\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "327e81fe",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "This figure compares overall NQS ratings against the SEIFA decile, which measures socioeconomic advantage and disadvantage of an area. The SEIFA metric is broken into ten groups, referred to as deciles, with 1 representing most disadvantage.  @cr-plot-rating-SEIFA-full\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {#cr-plot-rating-SEIFA-working style=\"width: 1000px; height: 500px;\"}"
      ],
      "id": "8bcb1c5f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "fig = plot_seifa_distribution(final_df_vic, highlight_rating = 'Working Towards NQS')\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "be804de1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "Areas with higher incidence of disadvantage have more services that do not meeting the NQS. @cr-plot-rating-SEIFA-working\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {#cr-plot-rating-SEIFA-exceeding style=\"width: 1000px; height: 500px;\"}"
      ],
      "id": "915075e7"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "fig = plot_seifa_distribution(final_df_vic, highlight_rating = 'Exceeding NQS')\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "135a2ef4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "The inverse relationship is true for services exceeding the NQS. @cr-plot-rating-SEIFA-exceeding\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {#cr-plot-rating-SEIFA-excellent style=\"width: 1000px; height: 500px;\"}"
      ],
      "id": "b2461cc5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "fig = plot_seifa_distribution(final_df_vic, highlight_rating = 'Excellent')\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "5eb2340e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "For 'Excellent' rated services, we see a two-peak distribution for the most advantaged and the least advantaged areas. For the least advantaged areas, this may indicate how needs-based funding, such as SRF, is being used effectively by some services to deliver high quality education and care. @cr-plot-rating-SEIFA-excellent\n",
        "\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "# Service Count and Types\n",
        ":::{.cr-section layout=\"sidebar-left\"}\n",
        "::: {#cr-plot-service-trend-all style=\"width: 1000px; height: 500px;\"}"
      ],
      "id": "6cdbf389"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "fig = plot_service_counts_timeseries(final_df, filter_ldc_psk = False)\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "7717d2c8",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "Growth in the number of services for the entire ECEC sector remains stead at around 1.5% YoY. @cr-plot-service-trend-all\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {#cr-plot-service-trend-vic style=\"width: 1000px; height: 500px;\"}"
      ],
      "id": "5c75e84a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "fig = plot_service_counts_timeseries(final_df, filter_ldc_psk = True)\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "318e97a4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "For kindergarten services (sessional and long day care), growth in the number of services is higher, but remains steady at 3% YoY. @cr-plot-service-trend-vic\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "For-profit operators remain the largest type of service provider, with this composition profile having remained almost the same over the past decade."
      ],
      "id": "088770c7"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| fig-align: center\n",
        "#| column: page\n",
        "fig = plot_management_type_stack(final_df_vic)\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "411747ca",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Sesssional providers are typically more likely to be non-profit, while long day care providers are more likely to be for-profit."
      ],
      "id": "fe16c8a1"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| fig-align: center\n",
        "#| column: page\n",
        "fig = plot_management_split_comparison(final_df_vic)\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ],
      "id": "136c8042",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
